{"name": "cubicweb-person", "metadata": {"name": "cubicweb-person", "version": "2.0.1", "classifiers": ["Environment :: Web Environment", "Framework :: CubicWeb", "Programming Language :: JavaScript", "Programming Language :: Python"], "home_page": "https://www.cubicweb.org/project/cubicweb-person", "license": "LGPL", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["cubicweb", "cubicweb-web"], "summary": "person component for the CubicWeb framework", "upload_time": 1691077067}, "documentation": ["Summary\n-------\n\n`person` provides person informations :\n\n- firstname\n- surname / lastname\n- civility\n- arbitrary text description\n- a relation to an email address (NB, the `EmailAddress` entity is\n  automatically provided by cubicweb).\n\nIf the `addressbook` cube is used, persons will also have *phone* and\n*postal_address* relations to store more contact information.\n\nThere is a special relation called 'primary_email'. A person can be linked to\nmultiple email addresses (using the 'use_email' relation). The primary email\nmust be unique. At the creation of the first email, this relation is\nautomatically added (though you can change it later, of course).\n\nRecommends\n----------\n\n- `addressbook` cube\n\n\nUsage\n-----\n\nIn addition of basic entity views, this cube provides :\n\n- *VCardPersonView*, displays a person in the VCard file format\n   (.. _VCard on wikipedia: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/VCard) .\n\n   This view creates a file called `vcard.vcf` which can be open in\n   your addressbook application (Kmail, Thunderbird and so on). In\n   order to generate this file, you have to access to a specific view\n   using an url address with `?vid=vcard` suffix.\n\n   How to personalize the person primary view in order to add a link\n   for the vcard ?\n\n   .. sourcecode:: python\n\n     class PersonalizedPersonPrimaryView(PersonPrimaryView):\n\n         def render_entity_attributes(self, entity):\n             super(PersonalizedPersonPrimaryView, self).render_entity_attributes(entity)\n             self.w(u'<div><a href=\"%s\">export contact as vcard</a></div>'  % entity.absolute_url(vid='vcard'))\n\n    This view will not be selected by default. You have to registered\n    this view or add a selector. For more information, please refer to\n    XXX in the doc.\n\n- a *civility facet*, this facet (XXX: ref to facet doc) will be shown\n  if a view displays a result set of at least two Person entities with\n  different civilities.\n\nContributing\n------------\n\nInformation on how to contribute can be found here https://www.logilab.org/Card/contributing\n"], "modules": [{"name": "cubicweb_person", "documentation": ["cubicweb-person"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.schema", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.Person", "bases": ["EntityType"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.Person.surname", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.Person.firstname", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.Person.civility", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.Person.description", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.Person.phone", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.Person.postal_address", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.Person.im_address", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["a physical person"]}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.use_email", "bases": ["RelationDefinition"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.use_email.__permissions__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.use_email.subject", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.use_email.object", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.use_email.cardinality", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.use_email.composite", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["person's email account"]}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.primary_email", "bases": ["RelationDefinition"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.primary_email.__permissions__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.primary_email.subject", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.primary_email.object", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.primary_email.cardinality", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.schema.primary_email.constraints", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["person's primary email account"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.__pkginfo__", "documentation": ["cubicweb-person packaging information", "pylint: disable-msg=W0622"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "cubicweb_person.__pkginfo__.modname", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.__pkginfo__.distname", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.__pkginfo__.numversion", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.__pkginfo__.version", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.__pkginfo__.license", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.__pkginfo__.description", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.__pkginfo__.author", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.__pkginfo__.author_email", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.__pkginfo__.web", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cubicweb_person.__pk